{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"# WS6-a â€” Gerrit LLM-Review voter integration (voter + REST vote + stub-Gerrit tests)\n\n## Why\nThe code-review capability (WS1â€“WS5) must be wired as the Gerrit `LLM-Review` voter: on\n`patchset-created`, run the four-pass gate over the change and vote `LLM-Review` via Gerrit REST,\nwith the deterministic block/advisory outcome mapping to the label. This story is the **codeable +\nstub-testable** deliverable (deliverable *a*): the adapter seam, vote-mapping, REST client, and\npatchset handler, all verifiable against a STUB Gerrit â€” before any live environment. The live\nend-to-end dogfood proof is split into WS6-b (blocked on the deployed AWS/Gerrit env).\n\n## What\n- `src/rebar/gerrit/` â€” a new package: the `code_review_decision` adapter over\n  `produce_code_review_verdict`, a Gerrit REST client (vote), a patchset-created handler, and the\n  staged opt-in + rollback config.\n- Everything is exercised offline against a stub Gerrit client (no network).\n\n## Scope\n- IN: the voter integration (adapter seam + vote-mapping + REST vote + patchset handler + staged\n  opt-in/rollback config + robot-comment vocabulary) and its offline stub-Gerrit tests.\n- OUT: the live dogfood proof (WS6-b, gated on the deployed env); the capability itself (WS1â€“WS5);\n  the CI \"Verified\" second vote (epic 1fa8); provisioning the `LLM-Review` label / submit\n  requirement / service-account (provisioned by d251 â€” this story CONSUMES them).\n\n## The adapter seam (the d251-S4b contract)\n`code_review_decision(diff_text: str, repo_root: str, ref: str | None) -> dict` wraps\n`produce_code_review_verdict` (WS4) and returns a receiver-stable shape:\n`{decision: \"PASS\"|\"BLOCK\", label_value: int, coverage_gap: bool, message: str}`. The d251\nreceiver consumes only `decision`/`label_value`/`message`; WS6-b's live receiver does not change\non swap.\n\n## Vote mapping (exact integers; all three verdicts covered)\n`produce_code_review_verdict` emits **three** verdicts â€” PASS, BLOCK, **INDETERMINATE** (LLM\noutage/degradation, or a fail-closed security abstain). The adapter collapses them to a two-value\ndecision, fail-closed:\n\n| verdict | decision | `LLM-Review` vote | note |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| PASS (advisory findings allowed) | PASS | `+MAX` (the label's max; satisfies d251's `=MAX` submit requirement) | advisory findings are surfaced in the robot comment but do NOT lower the vote |\n| BLOCK | BLOCK | `-1` (veto; blocks submit) | real finding |\n| INDETERMINATE | BLOCK | `-1` (veto) | **fail-closed** â€” a degraded gate never yields a submittable `+MAX` |\n\nThere is no `+1` case (the earlier `+1/MAX` notation is removed as ambiguous): a change either\nclears review (`+MAX`) or is vetoed (`-1`). `label_value` is resolved against the label's\nprovisioned MAX (config `gerrit_voter.max_vote`, default 1) so a `LLM-Review -1..+1` and a\n`-2..+2` label are both supported without code change.\n\n## Staged opt-in + rollback (the config gate)\nBecause a receiver processes Gerrit projects generically (not rebar's own repo_root), voter\nactivation is a **receiver-level** config, NOT the per-repo `verify.enable_code_review`:\n\n- New config section `[gerrit_voter]` (in the rebar-MCP receiver's `rebar.toml`; env overrides\n  `REBAR_GERRIT_VOTER_ENABLED`, `REBAR_GERRIT_VOTER_PROJECTS`):\n  - `enabled: bool = false` â€” the **master kill-switch** (rollback): `false` disables the voter\n    entirely regardless of the allowlist. Safe default OFF.\n  - `enabled_projects: list[str] = []` â€” the per-project **allowlist** of Gerrit project names. A\n    project is active iff `enabled AND (project in enabled_projects OR \"*\" in enabled_projects)`.\n    Empty list â‡’ no project active (safe default). `\"*\"` is the documented **fleet-wide** toggle.\n  - `max_vote: int = 1` â€” the label's provisioned MAX (see vote mapping).\n- **Lifecycle/ownership:** the config is a PR-gated file in the rebar-MCP deployment repo (single\n  reviewed source, no ad-hoc mutation). Adding a project = a reviewed PR appending to\n  `enabled_projects`; **retiring** one = removing it; **rollback** = flip `enabled=false` (or drop\n  the project). Disabling stops FUTURE votes; existing votes are left in place (Gerrit's\n  `copyCondition`, provisioned by d251, governs vote carry/reset across patchsets).\n- An inactive project (voter off / not allow-listed) â‡’ the handler returns WITHOUT voting (no\n  side effect), so activation is genuinely staged.\n\n## Robot-comment vocabulary (fail-closed vs real-finding distinction)\nEvery vote posts a robot comment whose FIRST line is a machine-parseable tag so an infra-failure\n`-1` is unmistakable from a real-finding `-1`:\n- `[LLM-Review: PASS]` â€” `+MAX`.\n- `[LLM-Review: BLOCK â€” finding]` â€” a real blocking finding (`verdict==BLOCK` with blocking\n  findings) â†’ `-1`.\n- `[LLM-Review: BLOCK â€” coverage-gap]` â€” a **fail-closed** `-1`: driven by\n  `coverage.llm_unavailable` (LLM outage) OR any `coverage.security_detectors[].reason ==\n  \"fail-closed-abstain\"` (a scanner could not run). The comment names the gap (which\n  scanner/what) so an operator reads it as \"re-run when infra is healthy,\" not \"your code is bad.\"\nThe tag vocabulary is a documented constant (`gerrit.voter.ROBOT_COMMENT_TAGS`) with a test.\n\n## REST vote failure behavior (non-happy path)\nThe Gerrit REST client mirrors the reconciler's transport posture\n(`_engine/rebar_reconciler/acli_rest.py`): urllib + Basic Auth (service-account token provisioned\nby d251), **retry on transient faults** (timeout / connection reset) with bounded backoff,\n**fail-fast on deterministic HTTP errors** (4xx/5xx â€” no retry). Outcomes:\n- Vote POST ultimately fails (network/auth/5xx after retries) â‡’ the handler logs the error and\n  returns a distinct `VoteError` result; **no `LLM-Review` vote is recorded**. This is safe: with\n  no `+MAX`, d251's `=MAX` submit requirement holds the change un-submittable (fail-closed by\n  construction â€” a missing vote never lets an unreviewed change merge).\n- The gate itself errors/times out (not the REST call) â‡’ `produce_code_review_verdict` already\n  degrades to INDETERMINATE â‡’ decision=BLOCK â‡’ `-1` + a `coverage-gap` robot comment (above).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `src/rebar/gerrit/` implements `code_review_decision(diff_text, repo_root, ref) -> {decision, label_value, coverage_gap, message}` over `produce_code_review_verdict`; the d251 receiver consumes only `decision`/`label_value`/`message` (seam test pins the shape).\n- [ ] Vote mapping is exhaustive over PASS/BLOCK/INDETERMINATE: PASSâ†’`+MAX`, BLOCKâ†’`-1`, INDETERMINATEâ†’`-1` (fail-closed); a test asserts each verdict â†’ the correct integer (no `+1` case; advisory findings keep `+MAX`).\n- [ ] A patchset-created handler assembles the change diff, calls the adapter, and votes `LLM-Review` via a Gerrit REST client â€” verified END-TO-END against a **stub Gerrit** (no network); the stub records the posted `{label_value, message}`.\n- [ ] Staged opt-in: `[gerrit_voter]` config (`enabled` master kill-switch default false; `enabled_projects` allowlist, `\"*\"` = fleet-wide; `max_vote`); a project is active only when `enabled AND allow-listed`; an inactive project â‡’ handler returns WITHOUT voting. Config schema + lifecycle/rollback documented; a test pins the active/inactive gate.\n- [ ] The robot comment distinguishes a fail-closed/coverage-gap `-1` (from `coverage.llm_unavailable` or a `fail-closed-abstain` security detector) from a real-finding `-1`, via the documented first-line tag vocabulary; a test asserts both tags.\n- [ ] REST-vote failure behavior: retry on transient, fail-fast on 4xx/5xx; a vote POST that ultimately fails yields a distinct error result and records NO vote (change stays un-submittable â€” fail-closed); a stub-driven test asserts this.\n- [ ] An ADR (0013) captures the Gerrit voter architecture: the `code_review_decision` seam contract, the vote-mapping (incl. INDETERMINATE fail-closed), the staged opt-in/rollback config, the robot-comment vocabulary, and the REST-failure posture.\n\n## Dependencies\n- CONSUMES d251's provisioned artifacts (label, submit requirement, copyCondition, service\n  account) â€” but this story's code + stub tests do NOT require the live env. The live proof is\n  WS6-b.\n- depends_on WS4 (98ff, closed) for `produce_code_review_verdict`.\n\n## Plan-review remediation (2026-06-30, Round-13)\n- BLOCK (config underspecified Ă—2): specified the `[gerrit_voter]` receiver-level config â€” format,\n  location, data model, master kill-switch, allowlist semantics, `\"*\"` fleet-wide, lifecycle,\n  ownership, retirement, rollback.\n- Advisory (split): split the dogfood into WS6-b (blocked on the live env); this story is\n  deliverable *a* only, closeable now.\n- Advisory (INDETERMINATE): added to the vote-mapping table + AC as a fail-closed `-1`.\n- Advisory (vote ambiguity): removed `+1/MAX`; exact integers stated (`+MAX` / `-1`).\n- Advisory (REST failure, rollback, robot-comment vocab, stub-test AC, ADR): each now has a\n  dedicated section + AC.","title":"WS6-a: Gerrit LLM-Review voter integration + stub-Gerrit tests"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782865304421943001,"uuid":"e25744bd-c797-49c7-ada7-564b616ec8f7"}